examplars:
Identify key points:
intent or purpose of the message (e.g. to inform, persuade, instruct);
the speaker's enthusiasm and passion for the topic;
main idea (s) and supporting points.
Read out and cross check the information written.

Make predictions about the content of a text using:
prior knowledge;
typographical and visual features;
text features;
organisational patterns;
organisational structure.
Ask questions to form ideas.
Answer questions to elicit understanding (meaning).
